'''Gem rocks''' can be mined through the [[Mining]] skill. A Mining level of 40 is required to mine gem rocks, granting 65 Mining [[experience]] per gem. 

Normal gem rocks can be mined in [[Shilo Village (location)|Shilo Village]] after a player has completed the [[Shilo Village]] [[quest]] or in the [[Lunar Isle mine]] after [[Lunar Diplomacy]]. The rocks regenerate 99 ticks (59.4 seconds) after being mined. Wearing a charged [[amulet of glory]] triples the success rate of mining these gem rocks.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/1326963791096111105|date=12 November 2020|archiveurl=https://archive.is/0DMWC|archivedate=12 November 2020|quote=You'd be 3x more likely to pass the mining roll at those rocks if you had a charged glory amulet.}} There is also another kind of gem rock which randomly appears during the [[Tai Bwo Wannai Cleanup]] [[minigame]] with a 5% chance per event.{{CiteTwitter|author=Mod Ash|url=https://twitter.com/JagexAsh/status/853301068901601280|date=15 April 2016|archiveurl=https://archive.is/Z67MK|archivedate=29 May 2020|quote=Nope, those are 5%.}} These rocks can be mined three times before they despawn.

The [[Shilo Village mine]] in the north-west part of the village has two sections: overground and underground. The underground section is only available for players who have completed [[hard Karamja Diary]], and it includes significantly more gem rocks than on the surface as well as a [[Bank Deposit Chest]]. For those who can only access the gem rocks on the surface, using a [[gem bag]] can extend trips.

[[Mining enhancers]] do '''not''' work on Gem Rocks.

